netgame.fivecarddraw

Class PokerGameState

  • java.lang.Object
    • netgame.fivecarddraw.PokerGameState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class PokerGameState
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Represents the state of a game of five-card-draw poker from one player's point of view. The full state of a game is kept by a PokerHub. That hub sends messages of type PokerGameState to each player whenever the state of the game changes. Note that the two players receive different messages, to reflect each player's view of the status of the game.
